Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.85,0:00:03.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The light of summer is the radiance of yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.69,0:00:05.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the tears is a yellow sunflower.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.89,0:00:07.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unexpectedly, a sad case has occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.32,0:00:10.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how skillfully it's covered up,\Nthe sunflower will be the sole witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.49,0:00:11.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.93,0:00:13.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.53,0:00:15.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.82,0:01:49.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.03,0:01:50.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.96,0:01:58.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just heard... Inoue Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}... was murdered!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.17,0:02:01.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim was an acquaintance of yours, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.51,0:02:04.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.97,0:02:06.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are no words to express how sorry I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.59,0:02:10.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was about to ask her to make me the happiest man on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.43,0:02:13.81,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Takaoka Akira (35)\NIndependent Film Director
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.12,0:02:13.81,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,For this to happen just when I was about to do that...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.14,0:02:17.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand how you must feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.10,0:02:20.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just who could've done this horrible deed?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.36,0:02:28.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, Inspector...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.16,0:02:30.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The estimated time of death is?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.12,0:02:32.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to the coroner...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.95,0:02:35.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was between 11:00 AM and 1:00 PM today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.10,0:02:53.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sunflowers, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.93,0:02:56.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} loved these flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.73,0:02:58.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.10,0:02:59.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You saw the culprit, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.81,0:03:01.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of person was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.44,0:03:03.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person that did such a thing to her...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.53,0:03:06.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just what kind of a person were they!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.37,0:03:22.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} ran a bar called "Sunflower."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.88,0:03:25.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've gone there often.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.51,0:03:26.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sunflower?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.97,0:03:27.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.38,0:03:31.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thrusting its chest out to the sun that beats down on it...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.93,0:03:35.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Upon seeing its image, she would be able to\Ngather the strength and courage to carry on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.47,0:03:37.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As a result, that's the legacy of the shop's namesake.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.56,0:03:42.72,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,And, when I went there yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.74,0:03:46.40,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,She said happiness had finally come to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.73,0:03:48.07,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Inoue Hiroko (38)\N"Sunflower" Bar Proprietor
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.46,0:03:48.72,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,She was already really overjoyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.53,0:03:50.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cheers!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.24,0:03:52.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did she mean, "happiness had finally come"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.96,0:03:53.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.16,0:03:58.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takaokda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} over there was Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s lover.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.67,0:04:02.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's worked on directing independent films for the past seven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.90,0:04:03.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And recently...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.42,0:04:09.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A large movie studio asked him to direct a film for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.80,0:04:17.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hear the movie was to be themed after the "crying-sands" of\NWhite Sands Beach, from his hometown in Fukushima Prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.60,0:04:22.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he went there by himself last night to\Ndo a preliminary inspection of the filming site.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.98,0:04:25.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} always believed in his talent...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.44,0:04:30.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Knowing his day would come, she had\Nbeen financially supporting him all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.12,0:04:38.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And just when those seven years of hard work had paid off...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.29,0:04:40.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's really a heartbreaking blow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.13,0:04:47.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Megure here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.75,0:04:53.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The old woman at the cigarette shop across the\Nstreet has been tending to her shop all day, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.01,0:04:57.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She says she didn't see anyone go in or out of the\Napartment complex around the estimated time of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.27,0:05:03.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only that afterwards, an electronics shop employee went\Ninto the complex with a large cardboard box, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.23,0:05:08.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was quite a while after, at approximately 4:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.60,0:05:11.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It appears it would have nothing to do with the current case, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.15,0:05:14.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Continue to gather information.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.24,0:05:16.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person next to Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.49,0:05:17.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Kitzuka Osamu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.74,0:05:19.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're both coworkers at a part-time job.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.04,0:05:23.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the one who discovered the body, and called 110.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.29,0:05:27.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who discovered Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was that person?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.13,0:05:28.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.63,0:05:29.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.73,0:05:32.36,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,He's hoping to become a scenario writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.22,0:05:36.34,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kitzuka Osamu (35)\NScenario Writer Hopeful
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.42,0:05:38.25,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Because Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had asked if he could borrow some story\Nideas from him, they arranged to meet in this room at 5:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.89,0:05:41.86,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The door was unlocked, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.60,0:05:43.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.89,0:05:44.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Kitzuka!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.98,0:05:48.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, has Takaoka come home yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.57,0:05:52.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.36,0:05:57.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After receiving the report, we arrived at 5:20.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.24,0:06:00.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A little before that, Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had arrived home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.08,0:06:06.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'd arrived about fifteen minutes later than the\Nappointed time due to being stuck in traffic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.13,0:06:10.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.88,0:06:12.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about Kitzuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.26,0:06:14.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, we've confirmed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.47,0:06:19.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was at his part-time job as a deliveryman for Oogata Electronics.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.39,0:06:23.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From 11:00 to 1:00, he was in the storeroom conducting inventory.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.64,0:06:25.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Kitzuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.44,0:06:30.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you came to this apartment, the door wasn't locked, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.82,0:06:33.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.86,0:06:37.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, I wonder if Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} forgot to lock the door...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.61,0:06:42.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because, usually, when women are home alone,\Nthey lock the door as a safety precaution.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.70,0:06:45.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She did often forget to lock the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.58,0:06:48.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If only I had warned her more strongly...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.50,0:06:49.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This sort of thing wouldn't have happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.30,0:06:58.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A comedy program is the only one that's been circled in red.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.22,0:06:59.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if it was so she wouldn't forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.55,0:07:02.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did she like comedy programs?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.31,0:07:04.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dunno...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.52,0:07:05.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That might have been the case though.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.65,0:07:14.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like she'd planned to watch\Nit today from 3:00 to 5:00 as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.65,0:07:18.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She wasn't even able to watch her favorite television program...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.86,0:07:20.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A random crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.32,0:07:23.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, something's off.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.70,0:07:26.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.08,0:07:28.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.12,0:07:29.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.33,0:07:30.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.92,0:07:34.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that a photograph of?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.05,0:07:40.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We asked for Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s alibi from 11:00\Nto 1:00, when Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was murdered...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.80,0:07:42.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was in Fukushima, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.35,0:07:43.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the filming site.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.35,0:07:45.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, at White Sands Beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.60,0:07:48.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, he said he didn't see anyone else there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.94,0:07:50.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.02,0:07:52.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So his alibi cannot be substantiated.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.94,0:07:56.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He mentioned that he withdrew some money at a nearby bank...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.19,0:08:01.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And through the White Sands Police Station,\Nwe confirmed that with this photograph.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.70,0:08:06.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was recorded on a security camera?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.95,0:08:09.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, looks that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.79,0:08:13.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd always felt uneasy around them because\NI felt like I was being watched, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.46,0:08:16.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess this time I should be grateful for the security cameras.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.42,0:08:19.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, it's not that we're suspecting you, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.09,0:08:22.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened after you went back to the hotel last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.97,0:08:24.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you meet with anyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.68,0:08:26.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no one at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.31,0:08:28.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.68,0:08:30.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.35,0:08:34.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At some point after midnight, I had room service come to my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.73,0:08:36.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.48,0:08:40.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't I take this chance to detail\Nall of my movement from yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.32,0:08:46.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We usually use this in meetings with the cameramen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.41,0:08:53.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As far as putting this down as a random crime, something's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.13,0:08:56.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sunflowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.01,0:09:04.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, this is what was bothering me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.01,0:09:07.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And also, the empty video case.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.77,0:09:15.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At 5:00 last night, I separated from Hiroko in front of the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.61,0:09:17.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.07,0:09:19.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was right when I had come to the shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.95,0:09:26.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't loiter around touching that stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.20,0:09:28.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.29,0:09:31.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This plug was probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.25,0:09:41.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I gave an interview at a newspaper company in\NFukushima a little past 10:00, if I remember correctly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.72,0:09:46.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are the business cards of the\Ncameraman and the reporter I met with.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.60,0:09:51.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These weren't removed in the normal way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.52,0:09:53.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did the culprit kick them out of the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.31,0:09:56.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or was it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.57,0:09:59.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.32,0:10:04.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I checked out from the hotel the next\Nmorning, at a little past 8:00 today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.28,0:10:06.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.41,0:10:08.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The voucher and the receipt, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.03,0:10:11.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At 2:27 in the morning, and the order was curry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.70,0:10:14.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s signature is also present.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.96,0:10:20.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In short, his alibi for the night is also proven without a doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.26,0:10:28.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew it, so that's how it was!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.93,0:10:32.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, the bank's security camera caught me at a little past 12:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.81,0:10:41.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, from last night to a little past noon today,\Nyou didn't set one foot outside of Fukushima, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.28,0:10:41.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.32,0:10:43.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.82,0:10:47.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A beautiful alibi with no flaws or time left unaccounted for!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.16,0:10:51.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't do that, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.66,0:10:52.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't just go around touching things!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.00,0:10:54.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.58,0:10:56.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But perfect timing!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.00,0:10:58.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I forgot that Uncle Kogorou asked for some things.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.08,0:11:00.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he wanted these investigated.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.17,0:11:03.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Investigated?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.05,0:11:05.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The inside of Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s bag and her shoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.01,0:11:11.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said they were important in determining who the\Nculprit is, so it was an extremely urgent request.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.98,0:11:23.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, here are the things you requested.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.65,0:11:26.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.45,0:11:29.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, earlier, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.49,0:11:31.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, where have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.91,0:11:34.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Prepare an investigation headquarters for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.49,0:11:38.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We need to take a look at the modus operandi\Nof each known burglar and look for witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.54,0:11:39.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.17,0:11:42.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've probably had the strength drained from you, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.29,0:11:48.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please, in memory of Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} as well as for your own sake,\Npull yourself together quickly and create a great work of art.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.22,0:11:52.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.56,0:11:54.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.22,0:12:01.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, through Detective Takagi's efforts,\Na number of true facts have been confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.02,0:12:01.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,True facts?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.98,0:12:02.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.32,0:12:04.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, Kitzuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.61,0:12:08.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you please take a look inside the video appliance for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.11,0:12:10.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.41,0:12:16.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a tape inside, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.33,0:12:17.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.04,0:12:18.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder what had been recorded.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.75,0:12:22.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you please rewind it a bit and play it back?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.79,0:12:24.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One, two.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.25,0:12:26.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One, two.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.09,0:12:29.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, isn't this a rerun?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.76,0:12:31.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I watched this program.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.76,0:12:32.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was about a month ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.72,0:12:34.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.93,0:12:40.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The overturned chair leg caught on the\Ncord, and unplugged it from the outlet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.31,0:12:44.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably during the struggle with the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.57,0:12:47.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, the fact that it had been recorded up until there...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.19,0:12:52.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit didn't know that Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had been recording it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.61,0:12:57.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It had been cut off about 3/4ths of the way into the 2-hour special.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.37,0:13:03.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It started recording at 3:00, and was cut off an hour and a half later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.75,0:13:07.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the room was thrown into disarray at approximately 4:30...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.00,0:13:10.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which is not the same time at which the murder took place, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.51,0:13:16.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thinking the culprit murdered Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} during the day, and then\Nreturned here again in the evening to rummage around for something...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.85,0:13:18.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a bit hard to imagine that being the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.89,0:13:24.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit murdered Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} between 11:00 and 1:00 at\Na separate location, and after transporting her body here...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.98,0:13:30.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Threw the room into disarray in order to make\Nit appear as if it was all the result of a robbery.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.53,0:13:40.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi, if you could give the thing you found to the Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.08,0:13:41.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.71,0:13:43.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, this is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.92,0:13:49.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like ordinary sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.09,0:13:53.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was found at the rear of Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s shoe, underneath the insole.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.26,0:13:53.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.93,0:14:02.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had the crime scene investigator research it and\Nhe said it was something called "crying sand".
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.56,0:14:03.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Crying sand?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.69,0:14:04.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.48,0:14:09.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With a high composition of quartz, a rare type\Nof sand that only exists at unpolluted beaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.07,0:14:13.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are twenty such beaches in the entire country.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.24,0:14:16.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of them is White Sands Beach in Fukushima Prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.07,0:14:22.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In addition, it is the beach at which\NTakaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was location hunting yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.12,0:14:26.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, perhaps you telephoned Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.04,0:14:28.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Likely saying something akin to...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.29,0:14:31.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I've finished location hunting, so how about you come over\Nhere to Fukushima so we can spend some time together?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.97,0:14:40.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Accordingly, Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} set up her recorder to record\Nthe comedy program she had wanted to watch...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.01,0:14:44.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And headed to Fukushima early this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.02,0:14:46.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The meeting time was after 12:00...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.65,0:14:50.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right after you showed yourself to the bank's security camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.20,0:14:59.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} got to the beach first.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.83,0:15:04.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because it was the beach which was to become\Nthe stage for the film her lover was to direct...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.04,0:15:08.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She probably had some special feelings for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.38,0:15:09.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.34,0:15:19.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The White Sands Beach is in your hometown.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.10,0:15:23.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were very familiar with the times\Nat which no one would be around.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.56,0:15:32.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, you quickly took off in your car and came\Nback to the area around this apartment complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.94,0:15:35.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You parked in a place where there were unlikely to be any witnesses...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.65,0:15:42.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, after dressing as a deliveryman, delivered the cardboard\Nappliance box containing the body to this apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.25,0:15:49.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so the electronics shop employee that was witnessed at 4:30...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.42,0:15:55.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you disguised using the uniform and hat\Nfrom the company you work part-time for, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.80,0:15:59.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, please stop that kind of talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.09,0:16:03.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't think that just because I was silently listening\Nto your story that I'd be taken to be the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.35,0:16:11.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me for a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.48,0:16:12.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.86,0:16:13.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you—?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.19,0:16:17.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It appears he just remembered something\Nelse I had asked him to investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.03,0:16:20.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, allow me to continue my explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.95,0:16:23.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having transported Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} here...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.99,0:16:32.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to make the scene look as if she had been murdered during\Nthe struggle with the burglar, you threw the room into disarray.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.96,0:16:37.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you disposed of the cardboard box,\Nthe hat, and the uniform somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.47,0:16:45.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, saying that you had been caught in traffic, you purposely\Nshowed up later than the meeting time with Kitzuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.60,0:16:47.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiroko...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.48,0:16:49.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiroko!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.39,0:16:55.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doing so, you made it seem as if\NHiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was murdered in this room...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.32,0:17:00.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that you could fabricate your alibi of having\Nbeen in Fukushima at the time of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.74,0:17:02.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.20,0:17:08.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, your deduction is that I called\NHiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to White Sands Beach...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.25,0:17:13.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then that I murdered her there between 11:00 and 1:00...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.25,0:17:15.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You seem to be under the impression that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.79,0:17:20.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, there really isn't any evidence that Hiroko went there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.55,0:17:21.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.88,0:17:26.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, please look inside the envelope\Nthat Detective Takagi brought here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.52,0:17:29.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.68,0:17:33.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's an article from this morning's issue\Nof the Fukushima daily newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.31,0:17:35.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably from the interview he gave yesterday
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.23,0:17:40.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That newspaper clipping was inside the pocket of Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.57,0:17:48.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After she arrived in Fukushima, Hiroko san had bought a newspaper\Nsince she knew that you had given an interview yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.24,0:17:52.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was just a brief mention, but since it was about you...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.16,0:17:56.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, it was the top news of the day,\Nmore important than any of the other articles.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.17,0:18:01.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a reward for her unwavering support these many years.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.38,0:18:06.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The flower bud had fully opened; the large sunflower had blossomed...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.30,0:18:10.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She probably treasured it with dancing emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.27,0:18:12.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.18,0:18:13.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiroko never came!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.73,0:18:17.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bought the Fukushima newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.02,0:18:20.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then I cut it out and put it in her bag...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.40,0:18:22.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.11,0:18:25.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you ever looked closely at the words\Nwritten on that picture on the wall?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.66,0:18:30.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Gazing only at you"...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.12,0:18:32.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the language of flowers, that is what sunflowers represent.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.96,0:18:35.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that was Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.87,0:18:37.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.33,0:18:40.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about if you admit your crime, and atone for what you've done?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.55,0:18:42.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's absurd!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.92,0:18:45.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did not murder Hiroko!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.60,0:18:50.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.85,0:18:51.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.23,0:18:53.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.73,0:18:59.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, please take a look!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.15,0:19:00.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sending you the image.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.40,0:19:02.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks to be sand, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.69,0:19:04.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,White sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.40,0:19:06.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.24,0:19:07.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There shouldn't be anything like that there!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.16,0:19:09.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I made sure that the blanket—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.29,0:19:12.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Made sure that the blanket" what?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.87,0:19:14.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What were you going to say after that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.83,0:19:16.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Was rid of all the sand," perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.92,0:19:19.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just a trace amount, but there is still some under the blanket.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.88,0:19:24.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, that sand is probably the\Nsame as the aforementioned crying sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.92,0:19:29.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please explain why there is some remaining in the trunk of your car.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.76,0:19:33.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you still saying that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.31,0:19:35.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That you really want to break up with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.23,0:19:38.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it because your luck has turned?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.06,0:19:39.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.02,0:19:41.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't say it's that simple!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.48,0:19:42.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel bad about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.53,0:19:45.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not a joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.40,0:19:49.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know just how much I've\Nsuffered through purely for your sake?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.24,0:19:51.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And now you're going to treat me as a burden?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.08,0:19:53.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll have you return the favor to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.58,0:19:54.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For the rest of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.96,0:20:00.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a spare key in Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.88,0:20:01.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I borrowed it for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.38,0:20:05.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.17,0:20:08.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Hiroko had intended to have me support her from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.26,0:20:11.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For me to be bound to her my entire life...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.35,0:20:14.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew I had to protect my independence somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.93,0:20:17.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.77,0:20:20.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your guesswork was amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.15,0:20:22.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You saw through my trick by sheer chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.27,0:20:28.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takaoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, take a look at the\Npotted sunflower on the floor there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.15,0:20:30.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you feel anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.99,0:20:37.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know how it was in Fukushima, but in this town\Nthere were no clouds—it was a beautiful Japanese day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.04,0:20:40.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so what of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.00,0:20:42.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This room faces south.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.71,0:20:47.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Additionally, the curtains were pulled back, so\Nthere was absolutely nothing to block the sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.51,0:20:51.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that potted plant had fallen between\N11:00 and 1:00, the time of death...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.51,0:21:00.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,During the time from then until 5:00, when Kitzuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} discovered the\Nbody, the sunflowers would have been exposed to plenty of sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.48,0:21:07.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sunlight is energy for sunflowers to bloom\Nin, so naturally the flowers would...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.99,0:21:08.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But here...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.99,0:21:12.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The flowers were face down, weren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.70,0:21:20.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of that, I surmised that the potted flowers were toppled\Nmuch later, perhaps right before the body was discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.21,0:21:23.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As such, I revised my reasoning accordingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.38,0:21:26.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, you figured it out well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.46,0:21:29.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, there is one flaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.72,0:21:33.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was after everything was over, and I was leaving...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.68,0:21:35.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That those sunflowers...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.94,0:21:45.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it was probably due to some sort of chance\Nthat the dirt inside had become unbalanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.61,0:21:49.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I never laid one finger on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.62,0:23:23.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it seems he said that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.58,0:23:27.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think you fell in order to make the truth known.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.08,0:23:28.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.17,0:23:30.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were the flower that had fallen from Hiroko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s fruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.25,0:23:32.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does Uncle have a customer?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.92,0:23:36.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm thinking it's like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.63,0:23:38.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.60,0:23:43.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sunflower is his captive audience...
